Notwithstanding Section 8.1, any Owner may elect, but only with the consent of the Owner or Owners accepting the Proportionate Share, to convey its Proportionate Share and assign its rights hereunder to another Owner or Owners and, thereupon, to cease to have any right, title or interest in the Common Facilities or its Proportionate Share; provided that: (A) the surrendering Owner executes and delivers all instruments of transfer as may be necessary or appropriate to effect (and that do effect) the conveyance of its Proportionate Share and assignment of its rights hereunder to, and which are reasonably satisfactory to, the remaining Owner or Owners, (B) such assignment and conveyance is accompanied by an assignment by the surrendering Owner to the remaining Owner or Owners of all its rights under this Agreement and (C) an encumbered Proportionate Share may only be surrendered with the written consent of each secured party that holds a security interest in such Proportionate Share and a release of such secured party's security interest therein. No surrender of an Owner's Proportionate Share shall relieve the surrendering Owner of any of its obligations under any agreement (including this Agreement and the obligation to pay its share of the Shared Expenses through the effective date of such surrender), unless expressly provided for in this Agreement, or agreed in a writing among the Owners. 8.3 Transfer Requirements. (a) Any sale, assignment or transfer made in accordance with Section 8.1 or Section 8.2 (i) shall relieve an Owner of any past obligation under this Agreement only to the extent consented to in writing by the other Owners, and (ii) shall relieve an Owner of any future obligation under this Agreement, only to the extent assumed by the transferee in writing. Except as permitted in Section 8.1, no Owner may transfer all or part of its rights to use the Common Facilities separately from its ownership interest in the Common Facilities. Any attempted or purported sale, assignment or other transfer of any interest in the Common Facilities or this Agreement made other than in accordance with this Article 8 either voluntarily or by operation of law shall be void and of no force or effect. (b) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary, no transfer of any Owner's Proportionate Shares or interests in this Agreement shall be effective unless and until the applicable Owner has obtained any necessary approvals from FERC and any state regulatory agency having jurisdiction over the Common Facilities (but only to the extent such consent or approval is actually required by any such agency). (c) [Reserved] (d) Each Owner hereby agrees to execute and deliver such instruments of conveyance, in recordable form as applicable, as the Common Facilities Manager deems necessary to vest ownership of such assignee's or transferee's Proportionate Share of the Common Facilities. 8.4 Obligations Regarding Liens. No Owner shall, directly or indirectly, create, incur or cause to exist any lien on or encumbrance (including a Permitted Lien) to be levied against or attached to the Proportionate Share of any other Owner and (b) no Owner shall create, incur or permit to exist any lien or encumbrance (other than Permitted Liens) on its Proportionate Share. If any such lien or encumbrance attaches or an Owner receives notice of any such lien or encumbrance, the Owner whose actual or alleged act or omission resulted in such lien or encumbrance shall cause such lien or encumbrance to be released and removed of record within fifteen (15) days of such attachment or notice, unless in the cause of clause (b) above, (y) such Owner (i) in good faith contests or disputes the validity of such liens or encumbrances, (ii) promptly commences legal action to remove such lien or encumbrance and (iii) furnishes to the other Owners a bond or other acceptable security in an amount sufficient to discharge all such contested liens and encumbrances and (z) during such period the lienholders' proceedings are stayed. If an Owner creates, causes or permits to exist a Permitted Lien on its Proportionate Share and there is a reasonable likelihood that such Permitted Lien will interfere with any other Owner's Proportionate Share in any material respect, then such Owner shall promptly remove such Permitted Lien upon such Owner's receipt of a written request therefor. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in accordance with Article 8, an Owner may grant a lien on or security interest in its Proportionate Share with respect to such Owner's Project and any Owner may obtain a judgment lien against any other Owner based on any such other Owner's breach under this Agreement, or otherwise permitted at law or in equity, and not specifically prevented by this Agreement. 8.5 Succession as "Owner". Any permitted purchaser, assignee or transferee (other than an assignee of a security interest pursuant to Section 8.1 prior to foreclosure thereon) shall be considered an "Owner" and a "Party" for purposes of this Agreement. 8.6 Lender Protection. (a) Parties' Obligations. Each Party agrees to consent to financing documents as may reasonably be required by Lenders. As a precondition to exercising any remedies related to any alleged default by a Party under this Agreement, any other Party shall give notice of the default to each Lender at the same time it delivers notice of the default to the first Party, specifying in detail the alleged default and the required remedy. Each Lender shall have the same amount of time to cure the default as is given to the first Party and the same right to cure any default as the first Party. The cure period for each Lender shall begin to run at the end of the cure period given to Parties in this Agreement, but in no case shall the cure period for any Lender be less than thirty (30) calendar days after receipt of the notice of default. The Lender shall have the absolute right to substitute itself for the first Party and perform the duties of the first Party hereunder for purposes of curing such default. Each Party expressly consents to such substitution, agrees to accept such performance and authorizes the Lender (or its employees, agents, representatives or contractors) to enter upon the Common Facilities to complete such performance with all of the rights and privileges of the first Party hereunder. (b) Lender Obligations. Any Lender that does not directly hold an interest under this Agreement, or whose interest is held solely for security purposes, shall have no obligation or liability to any other Party for performance of a Party's obligations under this Agreement prior to the time the Lender directly holds an interest in this Agreement, or succeeds to absolute title to a Party's interest. A Lender shall be liable to perform obligations of a Party to the other Parties under this Agreement only for and during the period it directly holds such interest. Any assignment permitted under this Agreement shall release a Party or other assignor from obligations accruing after the date that liability is assumed by a transferee, but the assigning Party shall continue to be liable to the other Parties for all performance due by the assigning Party for matters that have accrued and are unsatisfied as of the date of the assignment. Further in the event that a Lender elects to (i) perform a Party's obligations under this Agreement, (ii) acquire any portion of a Party's right, title or interest in all or any of the Common Facilities or (iii) enter into a new agreement as provided in Section 8.6(f), then such Lender shall not have any personal liability to a Party in connection therewith, and a non-defaulting Party's sole recourse in the event of a default by such Lender shall be to execute against such Lender's interest in the Common Facilities. Moreover, any Lender or other Person who acquires an interest in the Common Facilities pursuant to foreclosure or an assignment in lieu of foreclosure shall not be liable to perform any obligations under the Agreement to the extent the same are incurred or accrue after such Lender or other Person no longer has ownership of such interest. (c) Lender's Right to Possession, Right to Acquire and Right to Assign. A Lender shall have the absolute right: (i) to assign its Lender's Lien; (ii) to enforce its Lender's Lien and acquire title to the applicable interest in the Common Facilities by any lawful means; and (iii) to perform all obligations to be performed by a Party under this Agreement, or to cause a receiver to be appointed to do so. No Party's consent shall be required for any of the foregoing, and upon acquisition of an interest in the Common Facilities by a Lender or any other third party who acquires the same from or on behalf of the Lender, a Party shall recognize the Lender or such other party (as the case may be) as the other Party's proper successor, and this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect. (d) Opportunity to Cure. Following acquisition of an interest in the Common Facilities by the Lender as a result of either foreclosure or acceptance of an assignment in lieu of foreclosure, or by a purchaser at a foreclosure sale, this Agreement shall continue in full force and effect and the Lender or party acquiring title to such interest in the Common Facilities shall, as promptly as reasonably possible, commence the cure of all defaults under this Agreement and thereafter diligently process such cure to completion; provided, however, that the Lender or party acquiring title to such interest in the Common Facilities shall not be required to cure those defaults which are not reasonably susceptible of being cured or performed by such party. If a Lender is prohibited by any process or injunction issued by any court or by reason of any action of any court having jurisdiction over any bankruptcy or insolvency proceeding involving the defaulting Party from commencing or prosecuting the appropriate judicial or non-judicial proceedings, then any cure period for commencing such proceedings shall be extended for the period of such prohibition. (e) Termination. Neither the bankruptcy nor the insolvency of a Party shall be grounds for terminating this Agreement as long as all payments and all other monetary charges payable by the Party under this Agreement are paid by the Lender in accordance with the terms of this Agreement. (f) New Agreement. In the event that this Agreement is rejected or disaffirmed pursuant to bankruptcy law or any other law affecting creditors' rights, then, so long as a Lender has cured any such monetary default and is making commercially reasonable efforts to cure any such non-monetary default as provided herein, the non-defaulting Party(ies) shall, immediately upon request from such Lender received within ninety (90) calendar days after any such event, without demanding additional consideration therefore, enter into a shared use agreement with such Lender, which new shared use agreement shall (i) contain the same covenants, agreements, terms, provisions and limitations as this Agreement (except for any requirements that have been fulfilled by the Parties prior to such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance), and (ii) be for a term commencing on the date of such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance and continuing for the remaining term of this Agreement before giving effect to such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance. At the option of the Lender, the new shared use agreement may be executed by a designee of such Lender, with the Lender assuming the burdens and obligations of the defaulting Party thereunder. If more than one Lender makes a request for a new shared use agreement pursuant hereto, then the same shall be delivered to the Lender whose lien is senior in priority. (g) Lender Consent. Notwithstanding any provision of this Agreement to the contrary, (i) a Party shall not agree to a modification or amendment of this Agreement if the same could reasonably be expected to materially reduce the rights or remedies of a Lender or impair or reduce the security for a Lender's Lien, and (ii) a Party shall not accept a termination of this Agreement without the prior consent of each Lender. (h) Further Assurances. The Owners, the Common Facilities Manager and the Owners Committee shall exercise commercially reasonable efforts, at their own cost and expense, to (i) cooperate in amending this Agreement from time to time to include any provision that may be reasonably requested by a Party or any Lender to implement the provisions contained in this Agreement or to preserve a Lender's Lien, (ii) execute any documents which may reasonably be required by a Party or a Lender to give effect to a provision of this Agreement and (iii) reasonably cooperate with the interconnection of any Project, including as necessary temporarily curtailing or discontinuing deliveries of energy from any Project for such reasonably minimal period of time as is necessary to perform the physical interconnection of a Project to the Common Facilities. ARTICLE 9 DEFAULT AND REMEDIES 9.1 Demand for Payment or Performance. Upon failure of an Owner to make or cause to be made any payment when due and owing, or to perform or cause to be performed any other obligation to be performed by it, pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, the other Owners may make demand upon said Owner for such payment or performance. 9.2 Payment Defaults. If an Owner fails to make or cause to be made a payment when due and owing pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, and such failure is not cured by such Owner within ten (10) Business Days following the date on which such Owner receives a demand with respect to such failure made pursuant to Section 9.1, such failure shall, upon the expiration of such ten (10) Business Day period, constitute a default by such Owner for purposes of this Agreement. 9.3 Performance Defaults. If an Owner materially fails to perform or cause to be performed any material obligation (other than a payment obligation) to be performed by it pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, and such failure is not cured by such Owner within thirty (30) Business Days following the date on which such Owner receives a demand with respect to such failure made pursuant to Section 9.1, or, if it is not reasonably practicable to cure such failure within said thirty (30) Business Day period, then within a reasonable period following the date on which such Owner receives such demand provided cure is commenced within such thirty (30) Business Day period and diligently and continuously prosecuted to completion, such failure shall, upon the expiration of the applicable grace period pursuant to this Section 9.3, constitute a default by such Owner for purposes of this Agreement; provided, however, that if such obligation is timely performed under protest pursuant to this Section 9.3, a default by such Owner with respect to performance of such obligation shall not be deemed to have occurred. 9.4 Disputed Defaults. If an Owner disputes a default asserted against it by demand pursuant to Section 9.1, then such Owner may make or cause to be made payment of any sums in dispute or perform the obligation in dispute under protest and without prejudice to any rights or remedies that such Owner may have pursuant to any of this Agreement or at law or in equity. The Owner purportedly in default shall (i) deliver such protest in writing to each Owner making demand with respect thereto, (ii) specify in such protest the reasons upon which the protest is based and (iii) deliver a copy of such protest by first class mail to each non-demanding Owner. If such dispute is resolved in favor of the Owner upon whom demand was made, the Owner making demand upon such Owner shall, by means of appropriate adjustment of amounts payable by the Owners respectively pursuant to any of this Agreement, reimburse to such Owner the amount of any payments made under rightful protest and the amount of the costs and expenses incurred by such Owner in performing any obligation under rightful protest, each such reimbursement to be made, together with ten percent interest per annum, such interest to accrue from (and including) the date such payments were made or performance accomplished under rightful protest to (but excluding) the date of such reimbursement. 9.5 Interest on Late Payments. Any payment not made by a defaulting Owner when due and owing pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement may be advanced by any other Owner(s) and, if so advanced, the amount of such payments shall be repayable to such other Owners by the defaulting Owner with interest at the Late Payment Rate to accrue from (and including) the date such advance is made to (but excluding) the date of repayment of such advance by the defaulting Owner. 9.6 Remedies. (a) In addition to all other remedies permitted by law or under this Agreement (all of which shall be cumulative), following a default by an Owner, the non-defaulting Owner and its Lenders or other interest holders shall be entitled to pay any amounts due by the defaulting Owner, including, but not limited to, the defaulting Owner's portion of the Shared Expenses, and/or perform the obligations of the defaulting Owner, and the defaulting Owner shall reimburse the performing Owners for any and all amounts paid and/or costs and expenses incurred in paying such amounts and/or rendering such performance, plus interest at the Late Payment Rate. (b) If after the Effective Date (i) an insolvency proceeding has been commenced against an Owner and such proceeding continues undismissed for sixty (60) days or (ii) an Owner institutes an insolvency proceeding with respect to itself, or admits in writing its inability to pay its indebtedness generally as it becomes due or fails generally to pay its indebtedness as it becomes due, or any action is taken by an Owner for the purpose of effecting any of the foregoing or any analogous proceeding (collectively, "Insolvency Proceedings"), then if that Owner is the Common Facilities Manager, such Owner shall automatically be removed as the Common Facilities Manager as soon as the other Owner designates and appoints a replacement Common Facilities Manager. As soon as the Insolvency Proceedings are completed, a successor Common Facilities Manager shall be selected by the Owners Committee. (c) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, the Owners each acknowledge and agree that it would be prejudicial to the interests of the Owners under this Agreement if any Owner were to seek partition or any other type of division of the Common Facilities or file an action for such partition or division. Therefore, in consideration of such fact and for other good and valuable consideration, each of the Owners hereby waives and relinquishes any and all rights that it may have at any time or under any circumstance, including, without limitation, after a default by an Owner hereunder, to seek a partition or any other type of division of the Common Facilities. 9.7 Equitable Relief. The Owners agree that damages may be an inadequate remedy for a breach by the Common Facilities Manager or any Owner of its respective obligations under this Agreement, and that each Owner shall be entitled, in addition to all other remedies at law or under contract, to seek injunctive and other equitable relief, including specific performance, against any other Owner or the Common Facilities Manager to prevent or eliminate any such default. 9.8 Existing Liens Not Affected. No remedy or action taken pursuant to this Article 9 by a nondefaulting Owner in connection with a default by another Owner is intended to give rise to the creation of any lien, claim or encumbrance of any nondefaulting Owner that is prior to the lien, claim or encumbrance of any secured party under any mortgage, loan, credit agreement or other security agreement or instrument of indebtedness between such secured party and such defaulting Owner existing as of the occurrence of such default by such defaulting Owner, except to the extent permitted under such mortgage, loan, credit agreement, other security agreement or instrument of indebtedness. 9.9 Separate Defaults. Each act or omission to act that constitutes a default under this Agreement shall be treated as a separate default under this Article 9. 9.10 Real Property Rights Default. To the extent an Owner is a "grantee" under the Real Property Rights, including Easements, including as the holder of an undivided ownership interest, as a tenant-in-common therein, a default by an Owner and remedies by a non-defaulting Owner under the Real Property Rights shall be governed by the provisions of the respective Real Property Rights. ARTICLE 10 DISPUTE RESOLUTION 10.1 Dispute Resolution; Negotiation by Senior Management; Jurisdiction; Consent to Service of Process; Waiver of Jury Trial. (a) In the event of a dispute, action, suit or proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement or transactions contemplated by this Agreement, including any question regarding its existence, validity, interpretation, or termination (each a "Dispute") between the Parties, the Parties will use all reasonable efforts to reach a satisfactory solution by referring the Dispute to senior management of each of the Parties. Senior management of the Parties will meet as soon as possible, on no less than seven (7) calendar days' written notice, unless specifically agreed otherwise and shall negotiate in good faith. Senior management of the Parties shall examine any submissions by the Parties, and shall, if the Dispute cannot be resolved immediately, agree to convene for further negotiations aimed at resolving the Dispute. Should senior management of the Parties be unable to resolve the Dispute within thirty (30) calendar days after commencement of negotiation by such senior management, then the Parties shall be entitled to pursue any and all available remedies at law, equity or contract, in accordance with Section 9.6. (b) Any Dispute that cannot be amicably resolved by the Parties hereto under Section 10.1(a) shall be exclusively resolved in the New Mexico Courts in accordance with this Section 10.1. Each of the Parties hereby irrevocably and unconditionally submits, for itself and its property, to the exclusive jurisdiction of any New Mexico State court or federal court of the United States of America sitting in New Mexico, and any appellate court from any thereof (collectively, the "New Mexico Courts"), in any action or proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement, or for recognition or enforcement of any judgment, and each of the Parties hereby irrevocably and unconditionally agrees that all claims in respect of any such action or proceeding may be heard and determined in the New Mexico Courts. Each of the Parties further irrevocably consents to the service of process in any action or proceeding in such courts by the mailing thereof by any parties thereto by registered or certified mail, postage prepaid, to such Party at the address specified for such Party in Section 12.1. Each of the Parties agrees that a final judgment in any such action or proceeding shall be conclusive and may be enforced in other jurisdictions by suit on the judgment or in any other manner provided by Applicable Laws. (c) Each of the Parties hereby irrevocably and unconditionally waives, to the fullest extent it may legally and effectively do so, any objection which it may now or hereafter have to the laying of venue of any suit, action or proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement in any New Mexico Court. Each of the Parties hereby irrevocably waives, to the fullest extent permitted by Applicable Laws, the defense of an inconvenient forum to the maintenance of such action or proceeding in any such court. EACH OF THE PARTIES HEREBY WAIVES, TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, ANY RIGHT IT MAY HAVE TO A TRIAL BY JURY IN RESPECT OF ANY LITIGATION DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY ARISING OUT OF, UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT. EACH PARTY HERETO (A) CERTIFIES THAT IT IS RELYING ON THE WAIVER CONTAINED HEREIN AND (B) ACKNOWLEDGES THAT IT AND THE OTHER PARTIES HERETO HAVE BEEN INDUCED TO ENTER INTO THIS AGREEMENT AND THE TRANSACTION DOCUMENTS, BY, AMONG OTHER THINGS, THE MUTUAL WAIVERS AND CERTIFICATIONS IN THIS SECTION 10.1. 10.2 Continuation of Obligations. Pending final resolution of any dispute, the Parties shall continue to fulfill their respective obligations hereunder. 10.3 Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by and interpreted in accordance with the laws of the State of New Mexico without regard to conflicts of law principles. ARTICLE 11 INDEMNITY; LIMITATION ON DAMAGES 11.1 Indemnity. (a) General Indemnity. Each Owner (an "Indemnifying Owner") shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Owners (an "Indemnified Owner") from and against any and all losses, damages, liabilities, claims, judgments, liens, penalties, costs and expenses (including, without limitation, reasonable attorneys' fees), which may be imposed upon or incurred by such Indemnified Owner or asserted against such Indemnified Owner by any third Person (i) in connection with any material breach of this Agreement by such Indemnifying Owner (including, a material breach by such Indemnifying Owner of its obligations pursuant to the Interconnection Agreement as applicable to such Indemnifying Owner's Project) and any grossly negligent or willful misconduct by such Indemnifying Owner and (ii) subject to the terms of this Agreement, with respect to the Indemnifying Owner's Project Controlled Assets (collectively, "Losses"). (b) Operational Indemnity. Each Indemnifying Owner shall additionally indemnify, defend and hold harmless each Indemnified Owner from and against any costs, expenses or revenue loss incurred (including the cash value of any lost federal production tax credits and any penalties imposed on the Indemnified Owner owning a Project then existing or damages payable to a power purchaser, the TSP, or Transmission Owner by the Indemnified Owner) by such Indemnified Owner owning a Project then existing caused by any material breach of this Agreement by such Indemnifying Owner (including, a material breach by such Indemnifying Owner of its obligations pursuant to the Interconnection Agreement as applicable to such Indemnifying Owner's Project) (collectively, "Operational Losses"). (c) Contribution. Except for indemnities, liabilities or obligations to be borne in a manner other than in accordance with Proportionate Shares pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, in the event that an Owner bears more than its Proportionate Share of any liability or obligation arising in connection with the Common Facilities and such Owner would not be required to indemnify any other Owner for such liability or obligation pursuant to Sections 11.1(a) and (b) above (a "Shared Liability"), the other Owners shall reimburse the Owner that incurred the Shared Liability within ten (10) Business Days after written demand therefor, to the extent of such excess so that the Owners bear that liability or obligation in proportion to their respective Proportionate Shares. No Owner shall settle or compromise any claim with respect to a Shared Liability without the written approval of the other Owners. (d) The Indemnifying Owner shall pay all undisputed costs, expenses and/or revenue losses under this Section 11.1 within five (5) Business Days after the receipt of an invoice for the same. Except with respect to indemnification for amounts that are taxable upon receipt (including lost revenues), any amounts paid as indemnification under this Section 11.1 shall be (i) increased to take account of any tax cost incurred (including a gross-up to take account of the tax cost of such increase) by the Indemnified Owner arising from the receipt of payments pursuant to subsections (a) and/or (b) of this Section 11.1 and (ii) reduced to take account of any tax benefit realized by the Indemnified Owner arising from the incurrence of the Losses or Operational Losses with respect to which payments are made pursuant to subsections (a) and/or (b) of this Section 11.1. In computing the amount of any such tax cost or tax benefit, the actual combined federal and state tax rate applicable to the Indemnified Owner shall be used. The amount of any such tax benefit or tax cost that is deferred or will be realized over time (including, without limitation, depreciation or amortization deductions) shall be the net present value of the future benefits or costs, as applicable, using a discount rate equal to the mid- term applicable federal rate in effect on the day on which the related amounts are paid as indemnification under this Section 11.1. 11.2 Limitation on Damages. NEITHER ANY OWNER, INCLUDING ANY OWNER IN ITS CAPACITY AS COMMON FACILITIES MANAGER, NOR THE COMMON FACILITIES MANAGER, SHALL BE LIABLE (IN CONTRACT OR IN TORT, INCLUDING NEGLIGENCE, STRICT LIABILITY, INDEMNITY, AND WARRANTY) FOR SPECIAL, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES (OTHER THAN (i) THOSE COMPRISING A CLAIM BY A THIRD PARTY NOT A PARTY HERETO FOR WHICH A PARTY IS ENTITLED TO INDEMNIFICATION HEREUNDER AND (ii) ANY REVENUE LOSS, WHICH SHALL INCLUDE THE VALUE OF ANY LOST FEDERAL PRODUCTION TAX CREDITS PURSUANT TO SECTIONS 2.2 AND 2.4), AND IN CONNECTION WITH, ARISING OUT OF OR IN ANY WAY RESULTING FROM SUCH OWNER'S PERFORMANCE, NONPERFORMANCE, OR DELAY IN PERFORMANCE OF ITS OBLIGATIONS UNDER THIS AGREEMENT OR FOR ANY FAILURE OF PERFORMANCE RELATED HERETO, HOWSOEVER CAUSED, EXCEPT TO THE EXTENT RESULTING FROM OR PART OF A THIRD PARTY CLAIM WITH RESPECT TO WHICH THE OWNER IS REQUIRED TO INDEMNIFY PURSUANT TO SECTION 11.1. ARTICLE 13 MISCELLANEOUS 13.1 Several Obligations; Relationship of Parties. Except to the extent otherwise expressly provided in Section 6.1(b), the duties, obligations and liabilities of the Owners under this Agreement are intended to be several and not joint or collective, and no Owner shall be jointly or severally liable for the acts, omissions or obligations of any other Owner. Nothing contained in this Agreement shall be construed to create an association, joint venture, or partnership, or impose a partnership duty, obligation or liability, among the Owners. No Owner shall have a right or power to bind any other Owner without its express consent, except as expressly otherwise provided in this Agreement. The relationship of the Owners under this Agreement is that of tenants-in-common. Nothing in this Agreement shall be deemed to constitute any Owner as a partner of, or joint venturer with, any other Owner. The employees, agents, and subcontractors of the Owners, in performing the obligations of each respective Owner under this Agreement, shall not be deemed to be the agents or employees or subcontractors of any other Owner. Each Owner acknowledges that while the Owners may hold certain undivided interests in the Shared Real Property Documents, and as such, all Owners would be entitled to control the Shared Real Property Documents and their use, each Owner's right to occupy and use the Shared Premises is governed by and subject to this Agreement. 13.2 Regulatory Approvals and Assurances. Each Party acknowledges and agrees that the use of the electrical transmission lines, conductors, insulators and other equipment for the circuits that will serve the Projects and are included in the Common Physical Facilities under this Agreement as well as the payments contemplated under Section 3.1 of this Agreement may constitute the provision of electric service under the Federal Power Act. As of the Effective Date, each Owner and the Common Physical Facilities are eligible for the waiver in 18 C.F.R. 35.28(d)(2) of the FERC regulations. After the Effective Date, if required by FERC the Owners agree to cooperate with each other to file this Agreement with FERC for review, approval, or acceptance. 13.3 Term and Termination. The term of this Agreement shall commence as of the Execution Date and, except for terms that expressly survive the termination of this Agreement, shall terminate upon the first to occur of: (i) a single Owner becoming the owner of the entire ownership interest in all of the Common Facilities or (ii) the mutual agreement of all the Owners. For FERC filing purposes, this Agreement shall become effective on the later to occur of (a) the Effective Date or (b) the effective date designated by FERC when this Agreement is accepted for filing by FERC. This Agreement shall only be terminated as provided in this Section 13.3. 13.4 Abandonment or Decommissioning of a Project. After the Effective Date, in addition to the obligations of the surrendering Owner set forth in Section 8.2 and in the event an Owner desires to decommission and abandon its Project, and the Proportionate Shares of such Owner are not accepted or the obligations under this Agreement of the surrendering Owner are not assumed by another Owner in writing, the surrendering Owner shall, upon notice to the other Owners of its intent to abandon its Project, be responsible for its proportionate share (as determined by such Owner's Proportionate Share as of the date notice of intent to abandon and decommission its Project is given to the other Owners) of the costs and expenses of the removal and wind-up of the Common Facilities and the restoration of the shared premises as required by the Shared Real Property Documents (collectively, the "Withdrawal Costs"). The Common Facilities Manager shall administer the calculation, collection, and distribution of the Withdrawal Costs, as follows (provided, however, that if the Common Facilities Manager is the surrendering Owner, then the non-surrendering Owner(s) shall have the rights and perform the obligations of the Common Facilities Manager under this Section 13.4): (a) The Common Facilities Manager shall calculate the Withdrawal Costs and shall provide written notice of same to the surrendering Owner within forty-five (45) days after the Common Facilities Manager has received notice of Owner's intent to abandon its Project. (b) The surrendering Owner shall, within thirty (30) days of the receipt of the written notice of the Withdrawal Costs, pay the Withdrawal Costs to the Manager. The Withdrawal Costs shall be maintained by the Common Facilities Manager in a reserve account and used by the Common Facilities Manager for removal of the Common Facilities and the restoration of the shared premises when same becomes necessary. (c) Upon any failure to pay the Withdrawal Costs constituting a default hereunder, the applicable Owner shall automatically forfeit all of its Proportionate Share hereunder to the other Owners and shall immediately cease and desist from the use of the Common Facilities. The surrendering Owner further irrevocably appoints the Common Facilities Manager as its true and lawful attorney, with full power of substitution, for the sole use and benefit of the remaining Owners, but at the surrendering Owner's expense, to the extent permitted by law to exercise, at any time and from time to time while the surrendering Owner's default has occurred and is continuing, the power to sell, transfer, assign or otherwise deal in or with the Proportionate Share of the surrendering Owner or the proceeds thereof, as fully and effectually as if the Common Facilities Manager were the absolute owner thereof, provided that the Common Facilities Manager shall give to the surrendering Owner not less than ten (10) days prior written notice of the time and place of a sale or other intended transfer or disposition of any of such Proportionate Share. Any Proportionate Share of the surrendering Owner transferred or surrendered to the other Owners shall be allocated to each remaining Owner on a pro rata basis in accordance with each remaining Owner's Proportionate Share. 13.5 Distributions. All insurance proceeds from insurance maintained pursuant to Section 7.1, condemnation awards, proceeds from the disposition of assets (reduced by all out-of-pocket costs and expenses reasonably incurred in connection therewith), liquidated damage payments and other payments, credits and refunds received, in each case, attributable to the Common Facilities (but excluding payments, credits and refunds received under the Interconnection Agreement) shall be used by the Common Facilities Manager to repair or replace the Common Facilities or, if not applicable, shall be distributed to the Owners in proportion to their respective Proportionate Shares. 13.6 Distribution on Termination of this Agreement. In the event that the Owners decide to decommission all of the Projects and to proceed with the removal of the Common Facilities, the Common Facilities Manager shall take account of all the Owners' joint assets covered by this Agreement, including the Common Facilities, and joint liabilities pursuant to this Agreement and shall proceed with the liquidation thereof. The assets covered by this Agreement shall be liquidated under the supervision of the Common Facilities Manager as promptly as is consistent with obtaining a reasonable value therefor, and the proceeds therefrom, together with any assets distributed in- kind, shall be applied and distributed as follows: (a) To the payment of debts and liabilities of the Owners to third parties in connection with the Common Facilities which are then due and the expenses of liquidation. (b) To the setting up of any reserves which the Common Facilities Manager deems reasonably necessary for any contingent or unforeseen liabilities or obligations or debts not yet payable by the Owners in connection with the Common Facilities, including any reserves to pay costs associated with the decommissioning and removal of the Common Facilities. (c) Any sum remaining shall be distributed on a pro rata basis based upon each Owner's Proportionate Share as of the date of final termination of this Agreement. (d) The Common Facilities Manager shall have the right, in order to effectuate the liquidation of the assets covered by this Agreement to disconnect the Common Facilities from the SPS Switching Station and the Projects. 13.7 Uncontrollable Forces. No Owner shall be considered to be in default under this Agreement or in breach of this Agreement on account of any failure in the performance of any of its obligations under this Agreement, other than obligations of such Owner to make any payments that are due and owing pursuant to this Agreement, if failure of such performance is due to the occurrence of a Force Majeure Event. "Force Majeure Event," as used herein, means any act or event that delays or prevents an Owner from timely performing all or a portion of its obligations under this Agreement or from complying with all or a portion of the conditions under this Agreement if such act or event, despite the exercise of reasonable efforts, cannot be avoided by, and is beyond the reasonable control of, and without the fault or negligence of, the Owner relying thereon as justification for such delay, nonperformance, or noncompliance. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, so long as the following events, despite the exercise of reasonable efforts, cannot be avoided by, and are beyond the reasonable control of, and without the fault or negligence of, the Owner relying thereon as justification for such delay, nonperformance and noncompliance, Force Majeure Events may include: acts of God; actions of the elements such as heavy rains, floods, earthquakes, hurricanes, tornadoes, lightning, ice storms, landslides, mudslides, high winds of sufficient strength or duration to materially damage a Project or significantly impair its operation for a period of time longer than normally encountered by wind energy facilities under comparable circumstances; subsurface or other site conditions (including environmental contamination, archaeological or other protected cultural resources, and endangered species or protected habitats); explosion; fire; epidemic; sabotage; terrorism; transportation delays; unavailability of materials; an act of public enemy; war; blockade; civil insurrection; riot; civil disturbance or strike or other labor difficulty caused or suffered by an Owner or any third Person beyond the reasonable control of such Owner (or third Owner) or its Affiliates (even if such difficulties could be resolved by conceding to the demands of a labor group); system emergencies affecting a Project; or any restraint or restriction imposed by Applicable Law or any directive from a Governmental Authority, which by exercise of due diligence and in compliance with Applicable Law an Owner could not reasonably have been expected to avoid and to the extent which, by exercise of due diligence and in compliance with Applicable Law, has been unable to overcome (so long as the affected Owner has not applied for or assisted such act by a Governmental Authority). Any Owner or Common Facilities Manager rendered unable to fulfill any obligation under this Agreement by reason of a Force Majeure Event shall give notice of such Force Majeure Event promptly to each of the Owners and shall exercise due diligence to remove such inability and thereafter resume performance with all reasonable dispatch. 13.8 Run With the Land. The Parties hereby agree that all of the covenants, consents and agreements contained in this Agreement touch and concern the subject of the Shared Real Property Documents and are expressly intended to, and shall, to the extent allowed by law, be covenants running with the land and shall be binding and a burden upon each Owner's present or future estate in the Common Facilities and upon each of the Parties hereto from time to time, their respective successors and assigns as holders of an estate or interest in such real estate (including any Lender or other Person acquiring title from any such Person upon foreclosure or by deed in lieu of foreclosure), and shall benefit the Parties hereto from time to time and their respective successors and assigns. To the extent any of the provisions of this Agreement are not enforceable as covenants running with the land, they shall be enforceable as equitable servitudes. 13.9 Estoppel Certificates. Upon the request of an Owner, any Lender or the Common Facilities Manager, any other Owner, upon not less than ten (10) Business Days' notice, shall, if true, provide a certificate stating that (i) this Agreement is in full force and effect and has not been modified or amended (or if modified or amended, stating so), and (ii) to the actual knowledge of the certifying Owner, there are no defaults under this Agreement and no events that, with notice or the passage of time or both, could become a default (or if there are defaults, describing them in reasonable detail). The requesting Owner, and any purchaser, investor or Lender with respect to such Owner's portion of the Common Facilities, shall be entitled to rely on the truthfulness of the statements made by the certifying Owner in such certificate. The failure of the nonrequesting Owner to deliver any such certificate within such time shall be conclusive upon such nonrequesting Owner that (a) this Agreement and the rights granted hereunder are in full force and effect and have not been modified and (b) there are no uncured defaults hereunder. 13.10 Partition Waiver. The Owners agree that the Common Facilities are not suitable for partition. Accordingly, each Owner irrevocably waives any and all rights that it may have under Applicable Law to maintain any action, suit or claim for partition of all or any part of the Common Facilities. In the event that any Owner is an entity that distributes its interest in the Common Facilities and this Agreement to its members, shareholders, partners or owners voluntarily, in the course of dissolution or by operation of law, such distribution shall comply with all requirements of Article 8 of this Agreement, the distributees shall become Owners under this Agreement and each distributee shall be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including the waiver of any partition rights. 13.11 Amendments. This Agreement and the consents and other rights created by it shall not be modified or amended except in a writing signed by the Parties; provided however, that an Owner may amend the Exhibits hereto but only if such amendments or modifications could not reasonably be expected to adversely impact any other non-consenting Owners and could not reasonably be expected to materially reduce the rights or remedies of a Lender or impair or reduce the security for a Lender's Lien. Following any amendment to the Exhibits hereto the Owner(s) approving such amendment will promptly deliver a fully executed copy of such amendment to the other Parties hereto as well as a written description of the reason for the amendment and such Parties' certification that the amendment complies with the terms of this Section 13.11. For purposes of clarification, transfers or assignments otherwise permitted hereunder shall not be deemed amendments to this Agreement. 13.12 Further Assurances. The Parties agree to cooperate in executing any additional agreements or amendments reasonably requested by the Parties to implement this Agreement so long as they do not adversely affect the rights of the other Parties or violate the terms and spirit of this Agreement. 13.13 Condemnation. If all or part of the Common Facilities is proposed to be taken as a result of any action or proceeding in eminent domain, or is proposed to be transferred in lieu of condemnation to any authority entitled to exercise the power of eminent domain (collectively, a "Taking"), Common Facilities Manager or any other Owner receiving notice shall provide the other Owners (and if not originally in receipt of the notice, the Common Facilities Manager) with reasonable advance notice of any impending proceeding or meeting related to such Taking and shall not in the absence of all parties, or approval of the Owners Committee, settle with the Taking authority or agree on compensation for such Taking. This Agreement shall terminate as to any portion of the Common Facilities so condemned or taken (except in the case of a temporary Taking after the duration of which the Owner's Committee desires to continue the Agreement, and the Agreement Term shall be extended, in such event, by the duration of such temporary Taking). Any award or other compensation payable as a consequence of such Taking shall be paid according to the Proportionate Share as described herein. 13.14 Partial Invalidity. Should any provision of this Agreement be held, in a final and unappealable decision by FERC or a court of competent jurisdiction, to be either invalid, void or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect, unimpaired by the holding. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, the Parties agree that in no event shall this Agreement continue for a term that is longer than the longest periods permitted by Applicable Law. 13.15 No Third Party Beneficiaries. Except with respect to the rights of an Indemnifying Owner and the Common Facilities Manager (if not an Owner) as set forth herein, the covenants contained herein are made solely for the benefit of the Parties hereto and their respective successors and permitted assigns, and shall not be construed as benefiting any Person that is not an Owner. 13.16 Entire Agreement; Multiple Counterparts. This Agreement, including the Exhibits and Schedules attached hereto (all of which are incorporated herein by this reference), contains the entire agreement between the Parties hereto in connection with any matter mentioned or contemplated herein, and all prior or contemporaneous proposals, agreements, understandings and representations, whether oral or written, are merged herein and superseded hereby. This Agreement may be executed in multiple counterparts and delivered electronically (including via fax or PDF), all of which counterparts shall together constitute one and the same Agreement. 13.17 Memorandum. Concurrently with execution hereof, the Owner shall execute and deliver a Memorandum of this Agreement, which Memorandum shall promptly be recorded in the official records of Roosevelt County, New Mexico.
